Steller's jay



Although the campground entrance had a bear warning, the only wild mammals we saw were some squirrels and bats.
But there were plenty of birds: doves, hawks, Steller's jays, scrub jays, ravens, and woodpeckers.
Taken Saturday, August 18, 2001, 10:24:32am.  Original image size: 1600x1200, 1.1Mb
Technical details: Olympus C700UZ, 1/200s @ F3.5, ISO 185, 377mm
PS6 Crop, Curves 0:0 - 50:40 - 135:145 - 255:255, Unsharp Mask 6.0 70% threshhold 5
